HEADWORD: Refrication
<hw>Ref`ri*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(r?f`r?*k?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>refricare</ets> to rub again.]</ety> <def>A rubbing up
afresh; a brightening.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A continual <qex>refrication</qex> of the memory.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refrigerant</ent>⟦br⟧
